                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1162/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-03-15T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1926—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Your telegram number 126, March 13, 5 p.m. Department approves the
                    instructions to Canton as given in your paragraphs 2, 3, and 4.<note n="91"
                        xml:id="d564fn91">Apparently refers to last three paragraphs.</note> In the
                    judgment of the Department, military force should be employed only as a last
                    resort and only if considered to be absolutely necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
